					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">the eZ80 @ 50mhz is apparently stated to be equivalent to a z80 clocked to 150mhz when used with fast enough memory. eZ80 comes in various variations (ROMless, flash, sram, 20/50mhz). The price is normally 8-7, occasionally up to 12 EUR (for 50mhz variants) and down to 4,5 EUR (for 20mhz) when ordered by the hundreds. <br /><br />The 4510 has those two fancy CIA:s. Mouser and digi-key doesn't seem to have them in stock.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
