						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the eZ80 @ 50mhz is apparently stated to be equivalent to a z80 clocked to 150mhz when used with fast enough memory. eZ80 comes in various variations (ROMless, flash, sram, 20/50mhz). The price is normally 8-7, occasionally up to 12 EUR (for 50mhz variants) and down to 4,5 EUR (for 20mhz) when ordered by the hundreds. <br /><br />The 4510 has those two fancy CIA:s. Mouser and digi-key doesn't seem to have them in stock.</div><br />Yeah but I'm talking about this version which is a open source FPGA core <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://c65gs.blogspot.com.au/2016/04/overview-of-new-cpu-design-as-of-today.html">http://c65gs.blogspot.com.au/2016/04/ov ... today.html</a><!-- m --> he had to pull back on the 192Mhz version as people complained it wasn't 8bit feel still. 1Mhz 6502 is basically near to 3Mhz Z80, so a 48Mhz 4502/10 and a 150Mhz Z80 would be &quot;Game On&quot; <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

